text: Linstow or von Linstow may refer to: * Linstow AS, one of the largest companies of Norway * Dobbin-Linstow, a municipality in the Rostock district, in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany * Hans Linstow (1787–1851), a Danish-born, Norwegian architect * Hans Otfried von Linstow (1899–1944), a German Colonel who took part in the 20 July Plot to assassinate Adolf Hitler * Otto Friedrich Bernhard von Linstow (1842–1916), a German high-ranking medical officer and helminthologist
title: Linstow
